no reference here to moonrise (the cause of endless resultant debate in the commentaries about \softline
the precise hour that would then be indicated), but to the moon being high enough in the sky to \softline
dim the brightness of the stars at the approach of midnight.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab The moon, Dante would seem to be saying, was roughly on the same path taken by the \softline
sun when it sets in the southwest (when seen from Rome) in late November, between Sardinia and \softline
Corsica.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 82-84.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   The protagonist's gratitude to Virgil is expressed with a salute to his birthplace, \softline
Pietola ('Andes' in Roman times).  Some early commentators read the phrase 'pi{\f3 \'6a} che villa \softline
mantoana' to mean 'more than the city Mantua,' while the meaning is nearly certainly 'more than \softline
any Mantuan town,' i.e., any other town in the vicinity of the city, not Mantua itself, as Padoan \softline
